Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper discusses a bio-inspired computing paradigm for processing time-dependent signals, which is a characteristic of neural computing. 
2. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The paper presents a photonic reservoir computer, which is an emerging technology in the field of computing. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the effect of experimental noise on system performance, which is related to information theory. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the capacity of the photonic reservoir computer to generate periodic time series and emulate chaotic systems, which are tasks that are commonly tackled in machine learning. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of feedback in the photonic reservoir computer, which is a characteristic of control systems.
